The paper deals with power control and interference management in wireless networks, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a fixed-point iteration algorithm for power control, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the benefits of implementing the algorithm in a distributed fashion, which is related to game theory (cs.GT).
